<subSubSection id="9CA4653F0248FFF0FF65FC5C33C6FA05" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D40136B40248FFF0FF65FC5C32D6FA8D" blockId="2.[151,1134,968,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FF65FC5C3112FB9C" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1840" box="[151,336,1002,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cynocephala">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FF65FC5C3112FB9C" box="[151,336,1002,1029]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">C. cynocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fréquente les milieux ouverts comme les prairies ou pelouses non améliorées à proximité de cours d’eau ou de résurgences. Les larves minent les tiges de chardons, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FEC0FB99318FFBD1" box="[306,461,1070,1097]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Carduus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FEC0FB9931D4FBD0" box="[306,406,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Carduus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FE2FFB9932CDFBD1" author="Ball S. G. &amp; Morris R. &amp; Rotheray G. &amp; Watt K." box="[477,655,1070,1097]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref2462" refString="Ball S. G., Morris R., Rotheray G. &amp; Watt K. 2011. Atlas of the hoverflies of Great Britain (Diptera, Syrphidae). Biological Records Centre, Wallingford, 183 pp." type="book" year="2011">Ball et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Les adultes sont connus pour visiter les fleurs d’ombellifères blanches ainsi que celles des taxons suivants: 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FC56FBE73424FBF2" box="[932,1126,1104,1130]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Calluna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FC56FBE73424FBF2" box="[932,1126,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Calluna vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FF65FBC43115FB14" box="[151,343,1139,1165]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvense">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FF65FBC43115FB14" box="[151,343,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Cirsium arvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FE94FBC4320BFB14" box="[358,585,1138,1164]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Parnassiaceae" genus="Parnassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FE94FBC4320BFB14" box="[358,585,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Parnassia palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FDAAFBC532BFFB15" box="[600,765,1138,1165]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pulicaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FDAAFBC53287FB14" box="[600,709,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Pulicaria</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FCF8FBC53389FB15" box="[778,971,1138,1165]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Ranunculus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FCF8FBC533D1FB14" box="[778,915,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Ranunculus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FC2AFBC53425FB14" box="[984,1127,1138,1164]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FC2AFBC53425FB14" box="[984,1127,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Salix repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FF65FB223127FB36" box="[151,357,1172,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Saxifraga" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="azoides">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FF65FB223127FB36" box="[151,357,1172,1199]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Saxifraga azoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FE86FB233256FB37" box="[372,532,1172,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Scabiosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FE86FB23319EFB36" box="[372,476,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Scabiosa</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FDEDFB2232F3FB37" box="[543,689,1173,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FDEDFB22323BFB37" box="[543,633,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Senecio</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FD4FFB233316FB37" box="[701,852,1172,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FD4FFB23335CFB36" box="[701,798,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Sonchus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(Speight 2015). Son aire de distribution s’étend de la Scandinavie à l’ex-Yougoslavie et du sud de l’Angleterre au centre de la 
<collectingCountry id="ACA976240248FFF0FEBAFB6E31D5FB6B" box="[328,407,1241,1267]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Russie</collectingCountry>
. Sa répartition suisse connue s’étend du plateau aux zones non alpines ainsi qu’au jura (
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FE5DFB4C32CAFA8D" author="Speight M. C. D. &amp; Castella E. &amp; Sarthou J. - P." box="[431,648,1274,1301]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="1649 - 1917" refId="ref3179" refString="Speight M. C. D., Castella E. &amp; Sarthou J. - P. 2015. StN 2015. In: Syrph the Net on CD, Issue 10. Speight M. C. D., Castella E., Sarthou J. - P. &amp; Vanappelghem C. (eds), ISSN 1649 - 1917. Syrph the Net Publications, Dublin." type="book chapter" year="2015">Speight et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D40136B40248FFF0FF26FAAA33C6FA05" blockId="2.[151,1134,968,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
Bien que la présence de cette espèce, tout comme des deux autres, est déjà signa- lée au niveau helvétique (
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FE4CFA8832C3FAC1" author="Merz B. &amp; Bachli G. &amp; Haenni J. - P. &amp; Gonseth Y." box="[446,641,1343,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref2797" refString="Merz B., Bachli G., Haenni J. - P. &amp; Gonseth Y. 1998. Diptera-checklist. Fauna Helvetica. Centre Suisse de cartographie de la faune (CSFF) et Schweizerische Entomologische Gesellschaft (SEG), Neuchatel, 369 pp." type="book" year="1998">Merz et al. 1998</bibRefCitation>
), aucune mention de fréquence ou d’abon- dance pour la 
<collectingCountry id="ACA976240248FFF0FEC9FAD631C7FAE3" box="[315,389,1377,1403]" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Suisse</collectingCountry>
n’existe actuellement (
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FD7FFAD63337FAE3" author="Maibach A. &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau P. &amp; Dirickx H. G." box="[653,885,1377,1403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" refId="ref2734" refString="Maibach A., Goeldlin de Tiefenau P. &amp; Dirickx H. G. 1992. Liste faunistique des Syrphidae de Suisse (Diptera). Miscellanea Faunistica Helvetiae 1. Centre suisse de cartographie de la faune, Neuchatel, 51 pp." type="book" year="1992">Maibach et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FC7AFAD6342CFAE4" author="Speight M. C. D. &amp; Castella E. &amp; Sarthou J. - P." box="[904,1134,1377,1404]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="1649 - 1917" refId="ref3179" refString="Speight M. C. D., Castella E. &amp; Sarthou J. - P. 2015. StN 2015. In: Syrph the Net on CD, Issue 10. Speight M. C. D., Castella E., Sarthou J. - P. &amp; Vanappelghem C. (eds), ISSN 1649 - 1917. Syrph the Net Publications, Dublin." type="book chapter" year="2015">Speight et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
fournissent néanmoins une catégorie «menace» au niveau suisse.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CA4653F0248FFF0FF26FA1232BBF913" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="D40136B40248FFF0FF26FA1232BBF913" blockId="2.[151,1134,968,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
Le site dans lequel l’individu de 
<taxonomicName id="13BE4D370248FFF0FDB4FA1232B9FA27" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1840" box="[582,763,1445,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cynocephala">
<emphasis id="E6CAEAA60248FFF0FDB4FA1232B9FA27" box="[582,763,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">C. cynocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a été échantillonné était entouré de prairies artificielles extensives et intensives, mais aucun ruisseau, source ou résur- gence n’était présent. Il est donc probable que cette espèce provenait d’un habitat humide se situant au-delà du rayon de 
<quantity id="13469B510248FFF0FDC6F9BC323EF9BD" box="[564,636,1547,1573]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="200.0">200 m</quantity>
inventorié (par exemple de la zone humide de la Seymaz). Cela va dans le sens de ce qui est mis en avant par 
<bibRefCitation id="B02F4B450248FFF0FC63F99A347FF9DF" author="Haenke S." box="[913,1085,1581,1607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" pagination="1106 - 1114" refId="ref2702" refString="Haenke S. 2009. Increasing syrphid fly diversity and density in sown flower strips within simple vs. complex landscapes. Journal of Applied Ecology 46: 1106 - 1114." type="journal article" year="2009">Haenke (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, qui affirme que l’échelle paysagère à considérer pour appréhender l’ensemble des espèces peut être importante et parfois dépasser le kilomètre.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
